shoe_Description: The Nike Dunk Low “Hyper Cobalt” is a February 2021 release of the all-time classic silhouette that is inspired by an original Air Jordan colorway. The black and Hyper Cobalt leather panels on this Dunk are based loosely around the design of the “Royal” Jordan 1, a popular shoe that first appeared in 1985. Like the “Royal,” black leather appears on the perforated toe and on the mid-panel, collar, and heel of the “Hyper Cobalt.” Blue leather overlays on the forefoot, eyelets, collar, and heel pop against the neutral base. A Hyper Cobalt leather Swoosh appears on either side of the shoe and black “Nike” embroidery is stitched onto the heel. Blue “Nike” detailing appears on the branding tag on the black nylon tongue. Release date: February 18, 2021
